<br>
1) The thumb is in a physically POSSIBLE position, but not if this lady is holding a sword.  Her thumb should bewrapped around the sword and the other fingers, so it can support the full weight of the sword.  At this angle, the sword's weight on the thumb would be big.<br>
<br>
2) The hair looks ful an dbushy on the right, but flatter on the left.  If I were you, I'd make the hair less BIG on the right.<br>
<br>
3) Personally, I LIKE the feet.  &quot;Bricks with toes&quot; ?  oh, only a little.  The flat leather soles of sandals, however, usually extend past the toes, so we don't cut our toes or cover them in road-dirt.  Also, the top strap on the sandals goes down around the CENTER toe-- looks nice, but I've never seen it done that way before.  If she's meant to be an Earth person from a known culture, she should have the strap guided down between her big toe and the other 4 toes.<br>
<br>
P.S.  I'd raise the collarbone and the centerline on the neck, but leave the boobs where they are.  She's leaning forward and bringing her arms together, which is naturally going to make her boobs look low.<br>
<br>
P.P.S.  You did this in PENCIL ?  I assume there's a starter-sketch somewhere, with all the practice and mistake lines on it ?  Is this a tracing, done with vellum/onionskin paper over the first sketch ?  <br>
If this IS the first and only sketch, I'd love to know how you got such clean lines, with no mistakes. and no erase-marks.  MY pencil sketches are always a HORROR of tried-and-failed lines that couldn;t be erased completely, and the final lines look grey rather than black.<br>
